Pre-Game Insights: Malawi National Football Team hopes to redeem their pride against Senegal in the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.
Senegal are in pole position to take the remaining slot in Group L with a win over Malawi.
Malawi suffered a 4-0 defeat to Senegal in Dakar last Friday.
Malawi's coach Patrick Mabedi admitted that his team would play for pride against Senegal.
Flames captain John Banda stated they were geared to make the nation proud.
Goalkeeper George Chikooka will start following the red card to Brighton Munthali.
Senegal's interim coach Pape Thiaw acknowledged the challenge of playing against Malawi at home.
Senegal's squad includes key players like Sadio Mane, Nickolas Jackson, Pape Gueye, Ismaila Sarr, and captain Kalidou Koulibaly.
